<div class="grid-container grid-x body-content">
	<div class="cell large-12 small-12 main-content-well">
		<div class="story-content">
							<div class="story-info">
			<div class="featured-img-container">
			<img class="story-img" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/giftguideheader-copy.jpg" title="The Literary Hub Gift Guide: </br>50 Gifts for Writers">
								</div>
		<div class="story-heads">
		<h1>The Literary Hub Gift Guide: </br>50 Gifts for Writers</h1>
		<h2>Everything But Books</h2>	</div>
	</div>
										<div class="byline-date">
					<span class="byline"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/literary-hub/"  title="Literary Hub">Literary Hub</a></span>
					<span class="hr"></span>
					<span class="date">December 5, 2025</span>
				</div>
						<div class="story-body">
								<p>Writers can be hard to shop for. Like everyone, really. Would the writer in your life enjoy a novelty notebook that says &#8220;Eat, Pray, Read&#8221;? (<a href="https://lithub.com/i-beg-you-dont-buy-a-novelty-notebook-for-the-book-lover-in-your-life-this-holiday-season/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Probably not</a>, but you know them best, if indeed you do know them at all.) Would the writer in your life prefer an all-expenses-paid writing retreat, or perhaps <a href="https://lithub.com/literary-themed-cruises-with-famous-writers-are-apparently-a-thing-now/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">some kind of cruise</a>? (Likely the former, but as for the latter, it really depends on the strength of their stomach.)</p>
<p>If you&#8217;re clueless, you&#8217;re not alone. For the record, weÂ suspect that, no matter their individual proclivities, your personal favorite writer would enjoy positive online reviews, earnest praise, and/or your services turning their books face out in the bookstore, but alas, the best things in life cannot be linked.</p>
<p>So for those who like to wrap, Literary Hub is here to help, with fifty (50) suggestions, from the painfully practical to the absurdly frivolous, from the cool to the corny, from the obviously literary to more universal (but beloved by literary people, like our editors), from $6 to $6,000. The only rule is no books, because it&#8217;s actually impossible to buy books for writers. The ones they want, they usually already have.</p>
<p><a href="https://shopgenara.com/products/kaweco-al-sport-fountain-pen-olivine?_pos=1&amp;_sid=b2334f9e4&amp;_ss=r" class="external" target="_blank"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263550" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-literary-hub-gift-guide-50-gifts-for-writers/kawecoalsportfountainpenolivine2-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/kawecoALsportfountainpenolivine2-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="1620,1080" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="kawecoALsportfountainpenolivine2 copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/kawecoALsportfountainpenolivine2-copy-300x200.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/kawecoALsportfountainpenolivine2-copy-1240x827.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-263550" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/kawecoALsportfountainpenolivine2-copy.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="333" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/kawecoALsportfountainpenolivine2-copy.jpg 1620w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/kawecoALsportfountainpenolivine2-copy-300x200.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/kawecoALsportfountainpenolivine2-copy-1240x827.jpg 1240w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/kawecoALsportfountainpenolivine2-copy-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/kawecoALsportfountainpenolivine2-copy-60x40.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/kawecoALsportfountainpenolivine2-copy-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/kawecoALsportfountainpenolivine2-copy-50x33.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /></a></p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://shopgenara.com/products/kaweco-al-sport-fountain-pen-olivine?_pos=1&amp;_sid=b2334f9e4&amp;_ss=r" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kaweco Sport Fountain Pen</a>, $100</strong></h2>
<p>If your personal writer drafts by hand, you can&#8217;t do any better than this pen, which our Podcasts Editor Drew Broussard calls &#8220;the nicest pen I have ever used.&#8221; There are many varieties; Drew specifies the metal, but if you just want to dip your toe in, the <a href="https://www.atlasstationers.com/collections/kaweco-sport/products/kaweco-collection-sport-fountain-pen-sage-special-edition" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">plastic ones are about a third of the price</a>.</p>
<p><a href="http://https://libro.fm/"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263551" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-literary-hub-gift-guide-50-gifts-for-writers/images-114/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/images.png" data-orig-size="389,129" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="images" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/images-300x99.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/images.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-263551" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/images.png" alt="" width="389" height="129" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/images.png 389w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/images-300x99.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/images-60x20.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/images-50x17.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 389px) 100vw, 389px" /></a></p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://libro.fm/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Libro.fm Membership</a>, $15/mo</strong></h2>
<p>Writersâ€”especially writers with kids and/or long commutesâ€”love audiobooks, but we aren&#8217;t using Audible to listen to audiobooks anymore, girls. Senior Editor Jessie Gaynor has a Libro.fm membership on her wishlistâ€”it&#8217;s comparably priced and also supports any local bookstore you choose.</p>
<p><a href="https://pieceworkpuzzles.com/products/meta-puzzle" class="external" target="_blank"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263563" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-literary-hub-gift-guide-50-gifts-for-writers/metapuzzle_01_3a17d52c-e4f2-47bf-8b7b-de4fcaff4524-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/MetaPuzzle_01_3a17d52c-e4f2-47bf-8b7b-de4fcaff4524-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="1799,1520" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="MetaPuzzle_01_3a17d52c-e4f2-47bf-8b7b-de4fcaff4524 copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/MetaPuzzle_01_3a17d52c-e4f2-47bf-8b7b-de4fcaff4524-copy-300x253.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/MetaPuzzle_01_3a17d52c-e4f2-47bf-8b7b-de4fcaff4524-copy-1212x1024.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-263563" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/MetaPuzzle_01_3a17d52c-e4f2-47bf-8b7b-de4fcaff4524-copy.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="422" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/MetaPuzzle_01_3a17d52c-e4f2-47bf-8b7b-de4fcaff4524-copy.jpg 1799w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/MetaPuzzle_01_3a17d52c-e4f2-47bf-8b7b-de4fcaff4524-copy-300x253.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/MetaPuzzle_01_3a17d52c-e4f2-47bf-8b7b-de4fcaff4524-copy-1212x1024.jpg 1212w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/MetaPuzzle_01_3a17d52c-e4f2-47bf-8b7b-de4fcaff4524-copy-768x649.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/MetaPuzzle_01_3a17d52c-e4f2-47bf-8b7b-de4fcaff4524-copy-60x51.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/MetaPuzzle_01_3a17d52c-e4f2-47bf-8b7b-de4fcaff4524-copy-1536x1298.jpg 1536w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/MetaPuzzle_01_3a17d52c-e4f2-47bf-8b7b-de4fcaff4524-copy-50x42.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /></a></p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://pieceworkpuzzles.com/products/meta-puzzle" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Meta Puzzle</a>, $40</strong></h2>
<p>Managing Editor Emily Temple recommends pairing a Libro.fm membership with a puzzle (or several), for a relaxing evening activity perfect for writers who have been staring into a screen all day, and also who need a task they can actually finish (eventually). She likes both metafiction and metapuzzles, like the above, but any will do.</p>
<p><a href="https://appointed.co/products/pocket-note-pad?variant=40820743766127" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263552" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-literary-hub-gift-guide-50-gifts-for-writers/screenshot-2025-11-27-at-7-40-10-am/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-7.40.10-AM.png" data-orig-size="1224,818" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Screenshot 2025-11-27 at 7.40.10â€¯AM" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-7.40.10-AM-300x200.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-7.40.10-AM.png" class="aligncenter wp-image-263552" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-7.40.10-AM.png" alt="" width="500" height="334" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-7.40.10-AM.png 1224w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-7.40.10-AM-300x200.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-7.40.10-AM-768x513.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-7.40.10-AM-60x40.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-7.40.10-AM-50x33.png 50w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /></a></p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://appointed.co/products/pocket-note-pad?variant=40820743766127" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Pocket Notepad</a>, $10</strong></h2>
<p>Our Staff Writer Brittany Allen describes herself as &#8220;the unpaid spokesperson for all Appointed journal products,&#8221; so you can&#8217;t go wrong. This one will go wherever your favorite writer does; if they tend to be pocketless, Appointed also makes one that fits on a keychain. (There are regular sizes too.)</p>
<p><a href="https://literaryhub.myshopify.com/products/lit-hub-hat" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263556" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-literary-hub-gift-guide-50-gifts-for-writers/screenshot-2025-11-27-at-8-13-47-am/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-8.13.47-AM.png" data-orig-size="1354,1210" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Screenshot 2025-11-27 at 8.13.47â€¯AM" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-8.13.47-AM-300x268.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-8.13.47-AM-1146x1024.png" class="aligncenter wp-image-263556" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-8.13.47-AM.png" alt="" width="500" height="447" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-8.13.47-AM.png 1354w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-8.13.47-AM-300x268.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-8.13.47-AM-1146x1024.png 1146w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-8.13.47-AM-768x686.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-8.13.47-AM-60x54.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-8.13.47-AM-50x45.png 50w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /></a></p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://literaryhub.myshopify.com/products/lit-hub-hat" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Literary Hat</a>, $36</strong></h2>
<p>Thought we&#8217;d just slip this one in here. Now your favorite writer can inform all passers-by that she too is in on the joke.</p>
